---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Breadcrumbs from '../../components/Breadcrumbs.astro';
import CTABlock from '../../components/CTABlock.astro';
import { business, BASE } from '../../data/business';
import { postBySlug, postsBySlugs, RELATED_POSTS } from '../../data/posts';
import RelatedPosts from '../../components/RelatedPosts.astro';
import BlogHero from '../../components/BlogHero.astro';
import BlogFigure from '../../components/BlogFigure.astro';

const post = postBySlug('gutter-cleaning-cost-kilmarnock')!;
const relatedPosts = postsBySlugs(RELATED_POSTS[post.slug] ?? []).slice(0, 3);
const siteUrl = business.siteUrl.replace(/\/$/, '');
const url = `${siteUrl}/blog/${post.slug}/`;
const ogImage = `${siteUrl}${BASE}/gallery/kilmarnock-dry-verge-roof-repair-01-1600w.jpg`;

const articleSchema = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'Article',
  '@id': `${url}#article`,
  headline: post.title,
  description: post.description,
  inLanguage: 'en-GB',
  datePublished: post.date,
  dateModified: post.date,
  author: {
    '@type': 'Person',
    name: post.author,
    worksFor: { '@id': `${siteUrl}/#business` },
  },
  publisher: { '@id': `${siteUrl}/#business` },
  image: [ogImage],
  mainEntityOfPage: url,
  articleSection: 'Gutter cleaning',
  keywords: [post.keyword, 'gutter cleaning cost Ayrshire', 'blocked gutters KA1', 'gutter vacuum Kilmarnock', 'gutter cleaning price KA3'],
  wordCount: post.wordCount,
  about: { '@type': 'Place', name: 'Kilmarnock, Scotland' },
};
---
<BaseLayout
  title={`${post.title} | Sorn Handyman Services`}
  description={post.description}
  canonicalPath={`/blog/${post.slug}/`}
  ogImage={ogImage}
  ogType="article"
  extraSchema={articleSchema}
>
  <Breadcrumbs trail={[
    { name: 'Home', href: `${BASE}/` },
    { name: 'Blog', href: `${BASE}/blog/` },
    { name: post.title },
  ]} />

  <article class="container-x py-10 lg:py-14 max-w-3xl">
    <header>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center gap-2 text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-wider text-amber-600">
        <span>{post.area}</span>
        <span aria-hidden class="text-navy-900/20">·</span>
        <span class="text-navy-900/60">{post.readMinutes} min read</span>
        <span aria-hidden class="text-navy-900/20">·</span>
        <time datetime={post.date} class="text-navy-900/60">{post.dateDisplay}</time>
      </div>
      <h1 class="mt-4 font-serif text-4xl md:text-5xl font-black text-navy-900 leading-tight">
        {post.title}
      </h1>
      <p class="mt-5 text-lg text-navy-900/75">
        What actually drives a gutter cleaning price in Kilmarnock — house
        size, access, condition — what tells you your gutters are overdue,
        and how often you need it done. Every job priced individually —
        phone or WhatsApp for a free no-obligation quote.
      </p>
    </header>
    <BlogHero slug="kilmarnock-dry-verge-roof-repair-01" />


    <div class="prose-sorn mt-8 text-lg cv-auto">
      <p>
        A lot of the quotes people get for
        <a href={`${BASE}/services/gutter-cleaning/`}>gutter cleaning</a>
        come back with a "from" price. That is a hook, not a quote — the
        real number lands higher once the bloke has had a look. We price
        honestly from a photo across
        <a href={`${BASE}/areas/kilmarnock/`}>Kilmarnock</a>, with a firm
        number before we turn up. This is what goes into that number.
      </p>

      <h2>What drives the price in Kilmarnock</h2>

      <h3>Bungalows</h3>
      <p>
        A standard detached or semi-detached bungalow in a Kilmarnock postcode
        — KA1, KA2, KA3 — with one eaves run front and back, two downpipes
        and a single-storey reach is the simplest job we do. Every job priced
        individually and includes all gutters vac-cleared, downpipes flushed,
        photos of every run, and the moss and debris bagged and taken away.
        Hopper cleared, outlet flushed, bracket check while the pole is up
        there.
      </p>

      <h3>3-bed semis</h3>
      <p>
        The classic Kilmarnock 3-bed semi — think Onthank, Shortlees,
        Crookedholm, Bellfield, New Farm Loch — is two storeys, front and
        back eaves, plus the porch or bay window extra run at the front that
        catches leaves off the hedge. Same full service as the bungalow, just
        more linear metres on the vac pole.
      </p>

      <h3>4-bed detached</h3>
      <p>
        A 4-bed detached with a garage run, a conservatory gutter and a
        complex back roofline — common on the newer Riverside and Kilmaurs
        Road estates — takes longer on the pole. If the property has
        cast-iron deep-flow or an extra storey added in a loft conversion
        the price moves up with it. We are still on the ground with the
        vac pole; no ladders, no boot marks on the roof.
      </p>

      <h3>Victorian tenement or town-centre terrace</h3>
      <p>
        The King Street and Bank Street tenements in
        <a href={`${BASE}/areas/kilmarnock/`}>Kilmarnock town centre</a> are
        a different animal. Back-court gutters, cast iron, full of sixty
        years of silt. Priced individually against access and condition,
        and we will tell you honestly whether it needs clearing or replacing
        before we start.
      </p>

            <div class="not-prose my-8">
        <BlogFigure slug="ayrshire-fascia-board-repair-17" />
      </div>

      <h2>What pushes the price up</h2>
      <p>
        The four things that make a gutter job cost more than the baseline:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Height.</strong> Three storeys and up needs longer pole
          sections and a bigger vac — each extra storey adds to the price.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Length of run.</strong> A terrace with shared front gutters
          running three houses long is more metreage than the same-shaped
          semi.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Roof pitch and overhang.</strong> A low-pitch roof with a
          big eaves overhang makes the gutter harder to reach from the ground
          — sometimes needs an extension on the pole or a slight lean. Steep
          Victorian slates are the opposite — easy access, short reach.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Blockage severity.</strong> Light leaf debris is quick.
          Moss carpet, seeded plants, or a full silt layer takes longer and
          sometimes needs a water flush to finish. If it is extreme we will
          flag it in the quote before we start.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Signs your gutters are overdue</h2>
      <p>
        Before you book, walk outside on a wet day and look up. If you see
        any of these, book the clean:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Damp streaks down your wall</strong> directly under a joint
          or hopper. That is a leaking or overflowing gutter — water has
          been hitting the render for months.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Water overshooting the front edge</strong> during proper
          rain. The run is blocked or the gutter has dropped out of level.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Plants growing out of the gutter.</strong> Silt has built
          up deep enough to seed — that run is at least 50% full.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Damp inside an upstairs corner of the house.</strong> A
          classic sign water is backing up at the eaves and soaking the wall
          top.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Moss hanging visibly from the gutter lip.</strong> Hanging
          moss usually means a thick carpet inside.
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        If two of those are true, ring us this week rather than waiting for
        autumn. The damage compounds every storm you leave it.
      </p>

      <h2>How often to clean gutters in Kilmarnock</h2>
      <p>
        Once a year is the honest answer for most houses, and
        <a href={`${BASE}/blog/gutter-cleaning-ayr-kilmarnock-spring/`}>spring is the right window</a>,
        not autumn. The reasoning is long in that other post, but the short
        version: winter has already done its damage, spring moss lifts easier,
        and you get the summer to do any repairs you flag.
      </p>
      <p>
        Two exceptions. If you have mature trees within five metres of the
        roof — lots of Bellfield and Dean Park houses do — a spring
        <em>and</em> autumn clean is worth it. If you have no trees and a
        steel gutter-guard mesh, you can stretch to every two years.
      </p>

      <h2>What is included in the price</h2>
      <p>For every Kilmarnock gutter clean we do, the price includes:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>All gutters, hoppers and outlets vac-cleared.</li>
        <li>Downpipes flushed with water to confirm flow.</li>
        <li>Photos of each run before and after, sent by WhatsApp.</li>
        <li>All debris bagged and taken away — we pay the tip fee.</li>
        <li>Bracket and joint check while the pole is up.</li>
        <li>Free written quote for any repair we spot, no pressure.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        If we find a leaking joint, a sagging run or a broken bracket we
        will photograph it, quote a fix, and you decide whether to book it.
        That fits inside our broader
        <a href={`${BASE}/services/guttering/`}>guttering repair and replacement</a>
        work.
      </p>

      <h2>FAQ</h2>

      <h3>Do you use ladders on my lawn?</h3>
      <p>
        No. We use a gutter-vac pole system — a long carbon-fibre pole with
        a camera and a high-suction vac at the base. No ladder marks, no
        boot prints on the roof.
      </p>

      <h3>How long does a standard clean take?</h3>
      <p>
        Bungalow — under an hour. 3-bed semi — about ninety minutes. 4-bed
        detached — two hours. We show up, work, photograph, tidy, take
        payment by Stripe link or bank transfer.
      </p>

      <h3>Do you clean conservatory gutters?</h3>
      <p>
        Yes — and the conservatory roof itself where it is safely reachable
        from the ground with the soft-wash kit. Priced individually on top
        of the main house clean.
      </p>

      <h3>Can I get a quote without you coming out?</h3>
      <p>
        Yes. WhatsApp a photo of your house front and back with a rough
        note on storeys, and we will come back with a free no-obligation
        quote inside the hour — anywhere in KA1 to KA4.
      </p>

      <h3>What is the latest I can book for this spring?</h3>
      <p>
        We are booking about a week out in April and May. Phone or
        WhatsApp us today and we will slot you in.
      </p>

      <p>
        Book now, not in October. Your fascias — and your wallet — will
        thank you.
      </p>

      <div class="not-prose mt-10 rounded-2xl border border-navy-900/10 bg-navy-50/50 p-6">
        <p class="text-sm text-navy-900/60">Written by</p>
        <p class="mt-1 font-serif text-xl font-bold text-navy-900">{post.author}</p>
        <p class="mt-2 text-navy-900/75 text-sm">{post.authorBio}</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>

  <RelatedPosts posts={relatedPosts} eyebrow="Keep reading" heading="Related posts" variant="tinted" />

  <CTABlock
    heading="Ready to book a gutter clean in Kilmarnock?"
    sub="WhatsApp a photo of the house to Aidan or call Fraser — firm price back to you inside an hour."
    location="Kilmarnock"
  />
</BaseLayout>
